0 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   AC vsHP</span><hr size=1> I hear lots talking about being a HP this or that or a AC hound etc.  What I want to know is, do any of you use a formula for determining an AC Points worth of Hps?  How much HPs do you need to give up  a single AC point?  <br>
I see lots of warriors sportin crustacean armor these days.  I'd like to hear some comments on this armor.  In particular:<br>
<br>
Crustacean Shell Greaves<br>
MAGIC ITEM  <br>
AC: 12<br>
+4 STR, -4 DEX, +16 STA, -4 CHA<br>
WT: 7.5<br>
<br>
<br>
Crustacean Shell Vambraces<br>
MAGIC ITEM  <br>
AC: 10<br>
+8 STR, -4 DEX, +12 STA, -4 CHA<br>
WT: 6.5  <br>
These two pieces strike me as the best of the crustacean armors.  Each piece has a str and a good sta bonus.  But when you compare the AC of Crafted or Rygorr how does it stack up.  I am excluding the kunark warrior armor like cobalt and all othre high end armors.  When you can get those the AC is so good its not even debatable which you'd wear.  However in the lesser game.  Crafted, Rygorr Crustacean.  Can I get opinions on these and yer way of determining just how many HPS it takes to lose a point of AC.<br>
<br>
Thanks<br>
Bear<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/udaenerysoftargaryen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Daenerys of Targaryen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/24/01 12:21:23 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.drakonblayde.net/gfx/tarsig.jpg WIDTH=100 HEIGHT=150></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: AC vsHP</span><hr size=1> I'm really picky about AC and HP. Given the choices, I tend to take AC... that way it doesn't hurt so much when I start dropping AC for resist gear. OTOH, being a wood elf warrior, my hp's aren't quite as good as an ogre troll or barb... but they're good enough <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
 <p>=Daenerys Targaryen=<BR>
   =Jedi Warlord=
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/udalmoth.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dalmoth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/24/01 1:19:24 pm)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: AC vsHP</span><hr size=1> Give up AC for hit points primarily only when your dealing with big AE mobs or after your AC starts hitting the 1200 range. <p>Lie, Manipulate, and Crush them all.</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ugrimmlokk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grimmlokk</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.strike9.com/eq/Grimmlokk/fullsize/icon1.jpg BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 26<br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/25/01 2:16:47 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: AC vsHP</span><hr size=1>  I go 7.5hp = 1 raw AC generally. I'm a HP junkie though. Try starting at like 12hp for 1AC. See if you like the trade-off. <p><B>Grimmlokk</B><Forlorn><BR>
Warlord of E'ci<BR>
E'ci<BR>
<img src=http://www.strike9.com/eq/Grimmlokk/fullsize/bunnysig.jpg><BR>
<B>Pokewell Andoften</B><BR>
Hoe of the 51st poke<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=gangleri>Gangleri</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 30<br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/25/01 6:44:42 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: AC vsHP</span><hr size=1> This reminds me of a question I asked in the bunker : which is better? Crafted Bp or Enameled Black Cp.<br>
 When I was Level 43 or so the difference was:<br>
 Crafted ~ + 44 Hps<br>
 EBCP    ~ +  5 Ac<br>
<br>
  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ukobodaishi.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kobodaishi</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/27/01 11:00:29 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: AC vsHP</span><hr size=1> Kobo think AC is better. Kobo willing to sacrifice any hit point or attribute bonus for equivalent in AC. But when all the group is dead and Kobo faces many mobs alone because Kobo had AC, AC becomes moot. Kobo dies... but dies bashing,<br>
slashing, and piercing.<br>
<br>
Kobodaishi Sama<br>
40 Troll Warrior<br>
Silver Daggers <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ubearogfrostborn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bearog Frostborn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 107<br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/28/01 12:34:36 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: AC vsHP</span><hr size=1> Here is a shot of my stats in my typical group.  Level 48 shammy and level 49 cleric buffs.  AC is kinda low in the shot, not wearing my normal AC gear but maxing me HP cuz we are fighting mobs that hit FOR MAX no matter what yer AC is. BTW, we were successful in our endevor, I survived with about 133hps left.  The mobs hit for 123 to 156 most of the time, and the AOE's were between 450 and 500.<br>
